lldpMedConfigPortLocationCivicAddressWha.name: lldpMedConfigPortLocationCivicAddressWhat
lldpMedConfigPortLocationCivicAddressWha.description: This element describes which location the DHCP entry refers to. Currently, three options are defined: the location of the DHCP server (0: DHCP server), the location of the network element believed to be closest to the client (1: Switch) or the location of the client (2: LLDP-MED Endpoint). Option (2) should be used, but may not be known. Options (0) and (1) should not be used unless it is known that the DHCP client is in close physical proximity to the server or network element.
